cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

This paper deals with Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and their behavior in computer vision problems, specifically semantic segmentation and classification. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the behavior of deep networks, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of perturbations to improve performance is a novel idea, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper also discusses the performance of existing approaches, which could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
